DIV1.P:
Why shou'd we then be Laught out of Pudding and Dumpling? or why
Ridicul'd out of Good Living? Plots and Politics may hurt us, but Pudding can∣not. Let us therefore adhere to Pud∣ding, and keep our selves out of Harm's Way; according to the Golden Rule laid down by a celebrated Dumpling-Eater now defunct;
Be of your Patron's Mind, whate'er he says:
Sleep very much; Think little, and Talk less:
Mind neither Good nor Bad, nor Right nor Wrong;
But Eat your Pudding, Fool, and Hold your Tongue. PRIOR.
